      <title>Link: New Graphs for Gruff</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update&lt;/strong&gt;: Sorry, this isn&amp;#8217;t an update to Gruff, but an update to the CSS Graphs helper. Thanks &lt;a href="http://cwilliams.textdriven.com/articles/2006/05/25/css-graphs-plugin-patch"&gt;Chris&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://nubyonrails.com"&gt;Geoff Grosenbach&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href="http://podcast.rubyonrails.com"&gt;Rails Podcast&lt;/a&gt; fame is &lt;a href="http://nubyonrails.com/articles/2006/05/23/css-graphs-update-new-graph-types"&gt;updating Gruff&lt;/a&gt;, the excellent graphing library.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://nubyonrails.com/pages/gruff"&gt;Gruff&lt;/a&gt; is easy to &lt;a href="http://nubyonrails.com/pages/gruff"&gt;use&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://glu.ttono.us/articles/2006/03/29/spiders-invade-gruff-graphs"&gt;extend&lt;/a&gt;,
and makes really beautiful graphs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Go check it out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="http://thar.be/spider_small.png" alt="Spider Graph"/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
